Implemented and committed T-023.

Commit: `4aee449 feat(render): enforce wind voice lung capacity [T-023@20260416T181925Z]`

What changed:
- Added `LungCapacityRule` as render rule `R11` in `my-claw/tools/senseweave/render/rules/lung_capacity.py`.
- Wind/voice-style voices such as `breath`, `choir`, `sw_breath`, `sw_choir`, and named wind/voice markers default to `6.0s` lung capacity.
- Explicit `lung_capacity_s`, `lung_capacity_seconds`, or `lung_capacity` metadata overrides are clamped to `4.0s`-`8.0s`; `null`/`none`/`off` disables capacity.
- Non-wind voices such as `pluck` default to no lung cap.
- Continuous sounding time is tracked per tracker lane; over-cap passages tag/reuse an existing breath, insert a breath at the next phrase boundary, or convert a weak unaccented step into an earlier breath when allowed.
- Exported the rule from `senseweave.render.rules`.
- Added regression coverage in `tests/test_lung_capacity_rule.py`.

Validation run:
- `pip install -e '.[dev]'` passed.
- `pytest tests/ -x --tb=short` passed: `2902 passed`.
- `ruff check src/ tests/` passed.
- `mypy src/` passed.
- Also ran focused rule validation and direct ruff on the new `my-claw` rule file; both passed.

The remaining dirty files in the worktree are the pre-existing/unrelated `progress.md` and `sdp/` log/runtime files; I did not stage or commit them.

