ning)\\\\n+**Depends on:** Sprint 0 (Versioning System), Sprint 1 (Quality Scoring)\\\\n \\\\n-- **T-013** [T1] Create a production-course knowledge base that the composer can consult at runtime. (~3h) → deps: T-001\\\\n-- **T-014** [T1] Implement a verified pitch, interval, scale, and mode library. (~3h) → deps: T-001\\\\n-- **T-015** [T1] Add chord construction and voicing support. (~3h) → deps: T-001\\\\n-- **T-016** [T1] Encode functional harmony and modulation strategies. (~3h) → deps: T-001\\\\n-- **T-017** [T1] Expand rhythm, meter, groove, and time handling. (~3h) → deps: T-001\\\\n-- **T-018** [T1] Add counterpoint and linear voice-combination rules. (~3h) → deps: T-001\\\\n-- **T-019** [T1] Build a synthesis-architecture strategy registry. (~3h) → deps: T-001\\\\n-- **T-020** [T1] Add production-aware frequency allocation and EQ policy. (~3h) → deps: T-001\\\\n+- **T-029** [T1] Implement the Event dataclass with score-level, performance-level, reactive-delta, and provenance fields. (~3h) → deps: T-001\\\\n+- **T-030** [T1] Implement PerformanceIntent per-phrase metadata with arc shape, deviation bounds, tension target, restraint, and call/response role. (~3h) → deps: T-001\\\\n+- **T-031** [T1] Implement SectionEnvelope with breakpoint functions over tempo_base, density_target, dynamic_plane, brightness, tension_trajectory. (~3h) → deps: T-001\\\\n+- **T-032** [T1] Define IntentTag enum (build/settle/question/answer/withhold/punctuate) and require every phrase to carry one. (~3h) → deps: T-001\\\\n+- **T-033** [T1] Define Role enum (ostinato/melody/pad/perc/accent/silence) with grid_locked flag and role-filter policy used by all rules. (~3h) → deps: T-001\\\\n+- **T-034** [T1] Implement seeded-RNG architecture with per-stage sub-seeds derived from a root seed along a seed_path tuple. (~3h) → deps: T-001\\\\n+- **T-035** [T1] Refactor composition stage to emit score-tree with PerformanceIntent + SectionEnvelope + IntentTag metadata, deterministic from composition seed. (~3h) → deps: T-001\\\\n+- **T-036** [T1] Define the OSC/SuperCollider event contract that carries full Event metadata including rule_stack provenance through to the synth. (~3h) → deps: T-001\\\\n+- **T-037** [T1] Build a deterministic replay harness that reproduces any past performance from (score, composition_seed, interpretation_seed, delta_track). (~3h) → deps: T-001\\\\n \\\\n-*Subtotal: ~24 hours*\\\\n+*Subtotal: ~27 hours*\\\\n \\\\n ### Sprint 6: Stretch Goals\\\\n \\\\n **Depends on:** Sprint 0 (Versioning System)\\\\n \\\\n-- **T-021** [T2] Add post-tonal, spectral, and microtonal material strategies. (~6h)\\\\n-- **T-022** [T2] Build SuperCollider recipe references without coupling tests to live audio. (~6h)\\\\n-- **T-023** [T2] Add course-driven self-critique and revision targets. (~6h)\\\\n-- **T-024** [T2] Turn the production course into executable curriculum exercises. (~6h)\\\\n-- **T-025** [T2] Add operator diagnostics for production-course decisions. (~6h)\\\\n+- **T-038** [T2] Couple narrative engine to SectionEnvelope selection so dramatic arcs drive section choice. (~6h)\\\\n+- **T-039** [T2] Build audio-rendered SSM + Foote novelty cross-check via librosa on the actual rendered audio. (~6h)\\\\n+- **T-040** [T2] Establish listener-review workflow: weekly rendered pieces tagged with rule-stack provenance, ablation tooling documented for operators, review log template in place. (~6h)\\\\n \\\\n-*Subtotal: ~30 hours*\\\\n+*Subtotal: ~18 hours*\\\\n \\\\n ---\\\\n \\\\n ## Requirements Coverage\\\\n \\\\n-- **MUST requirements:** 20/20 covered\\\\n-- **SHOULD requirements:** 5 included as stretch\\\\n+- **MUST requirements:** 37/37 covered\\\\n+- **SHOULD requirements:** 3 included as stretch\\\\n \\\\n **✓ All MUST requirements covered.**\\\\n \\\\ndiff --git a/sdp/logs/Lead_T-011_20260416T054258Z_1776359763.log b/sdp/logs/Lead_T-011_20260416T054258Z_1776359763.log\\\\nindex cdf2015..115ca28 100644\\\\n--- a/sdp/logs/Lead_T-011_2026